<!-- ── Problems ── -->
<section class="problems-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:48px">
      <div class="section-tag">why jamjet</div>
      <h2>Production agents have<br/>unsolved problems.</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted);margin-top:12px;font-size:1.05rem;">Every team building real agent systems hits the same walls.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">RELIABILITY</div>
        <h3>Agents crash and lose everything</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">In-process orchestration libraries vanish on restart. No state, no recovery, no trace of what happened.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ durable graph execution with event sourcing</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">INTEROP</div>
        <h3>Agents are locked in silos</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">LangChain agents can't talk to AutoGen. CrewAI can't delegate to your partner's system. Everyone's isolated.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ native MCP + A2A protocols</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">OBSERVABILITY</div>
        <h3>You can't see what's happening</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">No cost attribution per node, no event timeline, no structured telemetry. Debugging is guesswork.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ OTel GenAI traces + checkpoint replay</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">SAFETY</div>
        <h3>Autonomous agents run forever</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">No standard way to enforce token budgets, cost limits, or iteration caps. Agents burn money until you kill them.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ compile-time autonomy constraints</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">PROCESS</div>
        <h3>Human approval is bolted on</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">Pausing for a human decision requires polling loops, external webhooks, fragile stateful callbacks.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ human-in-the-loop as a native node type</div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="prob-label">PERFORMANCE</div>
        <h3>Python orchestration doesn't scale</h3>
        <p class="prob-desc">GIL contention, asyncio overhead, per-call Python tax. Your orchestrator becomes the bottleneck.</p>
        <div class="prob-ans">→ Rust async scheduler, microsecond overhead</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="sep"/>

<!-- ── Features ── -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:48px">
      <div class="section-tag">features</div>
      <h2>Everything production demands.<br/>Nothing extra.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">durability</div>
        <h3>Durable Graph Execution</h3>
        <p>Every step checkpointed. Crash the process, restart it — execution resumes exactly where it stopped. Event sourcing + periodic snapshots.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">protocols</div>
        <h3>Native MCP + A2A</h3>
        <p>MCP client + server. A2A client + server. Connect to any tool server, expose your tools, delegate to or serve external agents — in your workflow YAML.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">humans</div>
        <h3>Human-in-the-Loop</h3>
        <p>Pause any workflow for human approval. Suspends durably — restarts and crashes don't lose the state. Resume via API, CLI, or webhook.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">identity</div>
        <h3>Agent-Native Identity</h3>
        <p>Every agent has a URI and an Agent Card describing capabilities. Managed lifecycle, discoverable via A2A, composable across orgs and frameworks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">observability</div>
        <h3>Full Observability</h3>
        <p>OTel GenAI traces. Per-node token and cost attribution. Structured event timeline. Checkpoint replay for any execution. Know exactly what happened.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">typing</div>
        <h3>Typed Schemas Everywhere</h3>
        <p>Pydantic, TypedDict, or JSON Schema for all inputs and outputs. No stringly-typed state. Schema violations fail fast at validation time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">autonomy</div>
        <h3>Configurable Autonomy Limits</h3>
        <p>Token budgets, cost caps, iteration limits, tool allowlists, approval requirements per agent — enforced at runtime with clear events and escalation paths.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">evaluation</div>
        <h3>Native Eval Harness</h3>
        <p>LLM-judge, assertion, latency, and cost scorers as first-class workflow nodes. Run <kbd>jamjet eval run --dataset qa.jsonl --fail-below 80</kbd> in CI.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-tag">performance</div>
        <h3>Rust Core, Python Authoring</h3>
        <p>Scheduler, state machine, and worker pool are Rust + Tokio. Workflows and tools are Python. Systems performance, developer ergonomics.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

